{
  "doc_id": "4412",
  "text": "On the contrary, many works tackle the observer-based control problem but in the disturbance free case. The problem of state reconstruction for system with delayed input has been addressed first in [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] . Then, their works have been extended to observer-based control. In [CITATION_3] , a predictive feedback control from the reconstructed states is designed. The problem of output feedback for nonlinear systems is addressed in [CITATION_4] but the designed controller does not involve any prediction. In [CITATION_5] , the controller is a Truncated Predictor Feedback (TPF) introduced in [CITATION_6] .",
